Indonesia hopes to dispel concerns about official corruption in relief operations by announcing each month the amount of money it receives in foreign donations and where the funds are being spent, the government said Tuesday.
Indonesia's death toll stands at almost 115,000, with thousands more still missing and hundreds of thousands left homeless after entire towns and villages were swept away or reduced to rubble by the quake and waves.
Indonesia was hardest-hit by the December 26 quake and tsunamis, with 110,229 confirmed deaths and 12,132 people missing as of Thursday, the social affairs ministry said.
